        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 30 at 6:09AM CDT by NWS Houston/Galveston TX</headline>
        <description>At 609 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 12
miles southwest of Elkhart, or 17 miles northwest of Crockett, moving
east at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Crockett, Grapeland, Latexo, Weches, and Mound City.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
